BigO of graphs:

for space complexity:

Adjecency Matrix: O( |V^2| )
Adjecency List: O(|V| + |E|)

where V represents Number of vertices and E represents number of edges.

Adjecency List >>> Adjecency matrix
--> As you only have to store the connected edges in the list 
contrary to storing all the connections in adjecency matrix

Adding an element:
Adjecency List: O(1)
Adjecency Matrix: O( |V^2| )

Adding an Edge:
Adjecency List: O(1)
Adjecency Matrix: O(1)

Remove an Edge:
Adjecency List: O( |E| )
Adjecency Matrix: O(1)

Remove an element:
Adjecency Matrix: O(|V| + |E|)
Adjecency List: O( |V^2| )
